Package hr.fer.zemris.java.simplecomp.impl.instructions

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractIncDec
    Abstract class for instructions that add a fixed value to a current value stored in a register.
    AbstractJump
    Abstract class for all variants of jump instructions.
    AbstractStack
    Abstract class for instructions that use stack.
    InstrAdd
    Add instruction adds numbers from 2 registers and stores the result into a third one.
    InstrCall
    Call instruction is used for calling a procedure.
    InstrDecrement
    Decrement instruction decrements the value stored in given register by 1.
    InstrEcho
    Echo instruction takes value from the register and prints it to standard output.
    InstrHalt
    Halt instruction expects no arguments and stops the program execution.
    InstrIinput
    Integer input instruction reads an Integer value from standard input and stores it in a given memory location.
    InstrIncrement
    Increment instruction increments the value stored in given register by 1.
    InstrJump
    Jump instruction performs an unconditional jump.
    InstrJumpIfTrue
    JumpIfTrue instruction performs a conditional jump.
    InstrLoad
    Load instruction loads from memory to one register.
    InstrMove
    Move instruction stores some value into a register or a memory.
    InstrMul
    Multiply instruction multiplies numbers from 2 registers and stores the result into a third one.
    InstrPop
    Pop instruction pops the last value that was pushed onto a computer's stack and stores it into a register.
    InstrPush
    Push instruction stores a value from a register onto a computer's stack.
    InstrRet
    Return instruction is used for returning from a procedure.
    InstrTestEquals
    TestEquals instruction tests if two registers contain the same values and sets the computer's flag accordingly.
